The Dataset has 503 Companies, Although called the S&P 500, the index contains 503 stocks because it includes two share classes of stock from 3 of its component companies.¶
From above we can conclude that there are 503 companies within 11 Industry having 123 Sub-industries¶
The Most company Industry is Information Technology which has 76 companies registered¶
The Most frequent Sub-Industry is Health Care Equipment¶
The Most common Headquater Location for a comapny is New York City, New York having 42 companies.¶

Q3 - Companies added each year into the index since its creation¶

In [ ]:
year = df['Date added'].dt.year.value_counts()
year.sort_index(inplace=True)
In [ ]:
a = []
year.index
for x in year.index:
    y = int(x)
    a.append(y)
In [ ]:
sns.set_style('dark')
sns.color_palette("cubehelix", as_cmap=True)


plt.figure(figsize=(22,12))
res = sns.barplot(x = a, y = year)
plt.title("Companies Added since the creation of S&P 500", fontsize= 20, fontweight = 'heavy')
plt.xlabel("Year", fontsize=18, fontweight = 'heavy')
plt.show()
